## What was accomplished

### New guide article — fragrance maceration / bottle aging

Added "The Resting Bottle: Does Fragrance Really Get Better With Age?" — a myth-busting
piece on maceration, oxidation, and storage. Debunks the forum claim that resting a
bottle for months improves it, while crediting the small real effect (a fresh batch
settling over its first weeks).

- Page: `src/app/guide/fragrance-aging/page.tsx` (~11 min read, 7 sections)
- Card: inserted into `src/app/guide/GuideIndex.tsx` after the `reformulations` entry
  (thematic neighbor — both about how a fragrance changes over time)
- Tag: "Myth-Busting · Science", category `guide`
- Voice: "knowledgeable friend" — informative, warm, light humor; matches citrus-woody
- Verified by live preview (Next dev on :3000): article and index card render correctly
  with all components (PullQuote/SectionLabel/Callout), amber accents, curly typography
- No fragrances named as links, so the slug-discipline rule has nothing to verify

### Worktree environment auto-link fix

Git worktrees don't inherit the main checkout's untracked `.env.local`, so `next dev` in
a worktree crashed (Supabase client got undefined URL/key → every route 500'd).

- Added `scripts/link-worktree-env.mjs` — locates the canonical `.env.local` via
  `git rev-parse --git-common-dir` and symlinks it into the worktree if missing
- Wired to `predev` in `package.json` (NOT `prebuild` — Vercel production builds inject
  env from the dashboard and must not run this)
- Safe by design: no-ops in the main checkout or if a `.env.local` already exists; never
  throws (dev is never blocked)
- The symlink itself is gitignored, so no secrets are committed

### Preview tooling

Added `.claude/launch.json` (fumage-dev → `npm run dev`, port 3000) for the preview
server. Untracked; `.claude/` is not gitignored, so it was intentionally left out of
commits this session.

